SWITZERLAND - British actor Roger Moore, who will forever be remembered for playing James Bond, died Tuesday aged 89, his family announced in a statement on Twitter.With the heaviest of hearts, we must share the awful news that our father, Sir Roger Moore, passed away today. We are all devastated. pic.twitter.com/6dhiA6dnVg"It is with a heavy heart that we must announce our loving father, Sir Roger Moore, has passed away today in Switzerland after a short but brave battle with cancer," they said.Moore is the longest-serving James Bond actor, playing the role seven times in the space of 12 years. He was also the oldest actor to play Bond, at 45 years.Moore was appointed a UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador in 1991 and voiced Father Christmas in the 2004 UNICEF cartoon The Fly Who Loved Me.In 1999, Moore was awarded a CBE and was eventually knighted in 2003 in recognition of his contribution to charity.Moore is survived by his three children, Deborah, Geoffrey, and Christian and wife Kristina Tholstrup. R.I.P. Roger Moore, you alligator-jumping legend. pic.twitter.com/po2KBC7FT9 The best Bond. RIP Roger Moore pic.twitter.com/Et3yAeADIu #RogerMoore was a LEGEND. Rest in peace, 007. pic.twitter.com/ebi4bgzdT2 RIP Sir Roger Moore, The Spy Whom We Loved pic.twitter.com/eSf4f4Zl5w Sir Roger Moore, who died today, in conversation with Parkinson and Wogan, about acting and his portrayal of James Bond. pic.twitter.com/KBzMofAZ1H Rest in Peace Roger -#rogermoore pic.twitter.com/Ld5SNniAz2 Sir Roger Moore, the film actor who has died aged 89, won international fame in the 1960s https://t.co/dN9gfnbtrR pic.twitter.com/o2t4hIHxnH eNCA